properties.Name: InventoryTransaction
properties.Description: A specific Inventory Transaction that is applied to or carried out at a specific Inventory Location(s) upon the Items in those locations.

Columns.Name: TransactionId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Transaction.

Columns.Name: TransactionRequestedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the Item Inventory Location Transaction was requested.

Columns.Name: TransactionPlannedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the Item Inventory Location Transaction was planned.

Columns.Name: TransactionInitiatedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the Item Inventory Location Transaction was initiated.

Columns.Name: TransactionCompletedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the Item Inventory Location Transaction was completed.

Columns.Name: TransitTime
Columns.Description: The time taken to move goods physically between different locations in a supply chain or laterally to another facility.

Columns.Name: FromWarehouseId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Warehouse.

Columns.Name: FromInventoryLocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a location.

Columns.Name: ToWarehouseId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Warehouse.

Columns.Name: ToInventoryLocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a location.

Columns.Name: StagingLocationRequiredIndicator
Columns.Description: An indicator that indicates that staging for the associated transaction at the inventory location is required.

Columns.Name: InventoryTransactionClassId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Inventory Transaction Class.

Columns.Name: InventoryTransactionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Inventory Transaction Type.

Columns.Name: InventoryTransactionStatusId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Inventory Transaction Status.
